# Add Package & Edit Package Full Pages

The screenshots show **Add Package** and **Edit Package** as full standalone pages (not modals). Currently these exist only as the [AddPackageModal](file:///c:/Users/hqbak/kenge/frontend/src/modals/AddPackageModal.tsx#15-224) modal component. We need to create two new page components and wire them into the router.

## Proposed Changes

### Pages

#### [NEW] [AddPackage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hqbak/kenge/frontend/src/pages/AddPackage.tsx)
Full page version of the Add Package form. Matches screenshot 5 — same form fields as the modal (Basic Information, Duration & Router, Bandwidth Configuration, Hotspot Settings, Additional Settings) but rendered as a page with `Cancel` and `Add Package` buttons at the bottom-right.

#### [NEW] [EditPackage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hqbak/kenge/frontend/src/pages/EditPackage.tsx)
Full page for editing a package. Matches screenshot 1 — same layout as Add Package but with:
- Title: "Edit Package" / subtitle: "Modify the settings for this package"
- Fields pre-populated from mock data based on URL param `:id`
- Buttons: "Cancel" (navigates back) and "Update Package" (red primary button)

---

### Routing & Navigation

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hqbak/kenge/frontend/src/App.tsx)
- Import [AddPackage](file:///c:/Users/hqbak/kenge/frontend/src/modals/AddPackageModal.tsx#15-224) and `EditPackage`
- Add routes: `/add-package` and `/edit-package/:id`

#### [MODIFY] [Packages.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hqbak/kenge/frontend/src/pages/Packages.tsx)
- "Add Package" button navigates to `/add-package` instead of opening modal
- Edit icon navigates to `/edit-package/:id` instead of opening modal
- Remove modal state/imports that are no longer needed

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. Run `npm run dev` in the `frontend` directory
2. Open the app in the browser
3. Navigate to `/packages` — verify "Add Package" button links to `/add-package`
4. On `/add-package` — verify the full page form renders with all sections, Cancel navigates back, form fields work
5. On Packages page, click Edit on a package — verify it navigates to `/edit-package/:id`
6. On `/edit-package/1` — verify the page loads with pre-filled data from mock, "Update Package" button visible
